How to setup backend?

Step 1:
-------
Clone the projcet

Step 2:
-------
Run project.bat from root folder of the cloned project.
./project.bat
This will bring up all mcp servers and mcp client

Optional: If you choose to test components individually. project.bat has all the below commands in a single file.
1. Bring up MCP Servers

    1.1 uf-mcp-server
        cd backend/uf-mcp-server
        ./compile.bat
        ./run.bat
    
    1.2 rts-mcp-server
        cd backend/rts-mcp-server
        ./compile.bat
        ./run.bat

    1.3 rag-mcp-server
        cd backend/rag-mcp-server
        ./run.bat

2. Bring up mcp-client

cd backend/mcp-client
./compile.bat
./run.bat

Step 3:
-------
How to test backend?

Install Bruno  (https://www.usebruno.com/downloads)
Click on Collection -> Open Collection 
Select backend/bruno

Select testChat
